<topic id="how-to-exist">
  <title>How to Configure an eXist Connection Using the Built-in Wizard</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Databases<indexterm>Connections<indexterm>eXist<indexterm>Connection
                wizard</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>eXist database<indexterm>Connection wizard</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To configure a connection for an <term>eXist</term> database using the dedicated
        <uicontrol>Create eXist-db XML connection</uicontrol> wizard, follow these steps:<ol>
        <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to
            <uicontrol>Data Sources</uicontrol> and click the <uicontrol>Create eXist-db XML
            connection</uicontrol> link.</li>
        <li>Enter your connection details in the connection wizard and click
            <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.<note type="important">To create an <term>eXist</term>
            connection using this wizard, <ph keyref="product"/> expects the
              <filepath>exist/webstart/exist.jnlp</filepath> path to be accessible at the provided
              <uicontrol>Host</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Port</uicontrol>.</note></li>
        <li>To view your connection, go to the <xref
            href="../topics/relational-database-explorer.dita#relational-database-explorer"
              ><uicontrol>Data Source Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>
          <ph conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/reopen-view-parenthesis"/> or switch to the
            <uicontrol>Database</uicontrol>
          <xref keyref="glossentry_perspective"><term>perspective</term></xref>.</li>
      </ol></p>
    <note type="important">If you are using <ph keyref="product"/> version 22.1 or newer and want to
      connect to an Exist 4.x or older database, the connection might fail. In this case, go to
        <uicontrol>Data Sources</uicontrol> preferences page, edit the Exist data source, and from
      the driver files list, remove the references to the <filepath>log4j-api-*.jar</filepath> and
        <filepath>log4j-core-*.jar</filepath> libraries.</note>
  </body>
</topic>
